<dl id="n09102f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09102f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09102f"> 102(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> with equal fury &amp; / devotion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If this Punic war <font color="green">[between the churches of Rome and Carthage]</font> was carried on without any effusion of blood, it was owing much less to the moderation than to the weakness of the contending prelates. Invectives and excommunications were their only weapons; and these, during the progress of the whole controversy, they hurled against each other <mark>with equal fury and devotion</mark> <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) I, (Chapter XV) 476</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
